<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-407-888  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 407 888.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The LocalNetter  Nov 1990 v10 n11 p213(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Architecture Technology Corp. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Gandalf takes 10BASE-T plunge. (Gandalf Data Inc's mini MAUtransceiver) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Gandalf Data Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Gandalf Data Media Access Unit (Transceiver) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionTransceivers (Computer Networks)10BaseT.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Gandalf's new miniaturized 10BASE-T mini MAU (Media Access Unit) transceiverallows devices to be connected directly to 10BASE-T local area networks(LANS) using unshielded twisted pair wiring, eliminating the need forexpensive stand-alone transceivers and transceiver cables.andM;The first in a planned series of 10BASE-T compatible products, the low-costGandalf transceiver lets users connect to 10BASE-T LANs by means of theirexisting IEEE 802.3 or Ethernet network interface cards (NICS) which do notcomply with 10BASE-T, retaining those investments.andP;  The mini MAU transceiveris compatible with all IEEE 802.3 and Ethernet NICs as well as with all10BASE-T wiring hubs, including Gandalf's StarPair system as well as itsAccess Hub systems,-which will be introduced in the near future.andM;Gandalf is demonstrating the compact device (1.9511 x 0.8511 x 2.811) at itsexhibit, Booth 819, at PC EXPO, scheduled to run through Sept. 27 here atMcCormick Place North.andM;The mini MAU transceiver is designed for easy use.andP;  It simply connects to the15-pin attachment unit interface (AUI) port of any IEEE 802.3 or EthernetNIC.andM;Four diagnostic indicators provide users with critical information on thestatus of the network connection.andM;The Gandalf mini MAU transceiver is available for immediate delivery, at$189.andM;For further information contact:  Janice Drummond or Alastair Davie, GandalfData, Inc., 1020 South Noel Avenue, Wheeling, IL 60090; (708) 459-9348.andM;Codenoll Announces And Begins Shipping Fiber Optic Ethernet Adapter Cards ForMicro Channel Personal ComputersandM;Codenoll Technology Corporation (NASDAQ: CODN) today announced three highperformance fiber optic Ethernet Micro Channel adapter cards for IBM PS/2personal computers and compatibles.andM;With this introduction of the new CodeNet-832X cards, which are available forimmediate shipment, Codenoll now offers fiber optic Ethernet network supportfor ISA (IBM PC XT, AT and compatibles), EISA (Compaq, Hewlett-Packard,Olivetti and others) and Micro Channel computers.andM;&quot;The design of the CodeNet-832X combined with the Micro Channel architecture,make this one of the fastest Ethernet interfaces available today,&quot; saidMichael H. Coden, president of Codenoll.andP;  &quot;As the first in a line of fiberoptic network adapters for the PS/2 and other Micro Channel computers, thesecards are another part of Codenoll's plan to support open systems andindustry standards such as Ethernet and the PS/2.&quot;andM;The new series of Micro Channel adapters consists of three cards:andM;1.andP;  CodeNet-8320, which uses a low cost passive star to create an economicalnetwork that retains the distance, performance, security and expandabilityadvantages of fiber.andM;2.andP;  CodeNet-8321, an Ethernet FOIRL-standard interface that connects toCodenoll's active star or any other FOIRL hub.andM;3.andP;  CodeNet-8322, which connects PS/2 performance to existing Codenollpassive star networks.andM;The suggested retail price for either the CodeNet-8320 or the CodeNet-8321 is$895.andP;  The CodeNet-8322 lists for $995.andP;  The new cards are availableimmediately in limited quantities with volume production beginning inmid-July.andM;The CodeNet-832X cards have a 16-bit data bus interface and onboarddual-ported 16-Kbyte memory that is shared with the computer's processor forhigh throughput.andP;  They support 10 megabits-per-second network datatransmission using CSMA/CD as specified by the IEEE 802.3 Ethernet standard.andM;For further information contact:  Brian Ramsey, Codenoll TechnologyCorporation, 1086 North Broadway, Yonkers, NY 10701; (914) 965-6300.andO;</TEXT></DOC>